Package edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_review.model.paper

Class Paper

java.lang.Object
edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_review.model.paper.Paper
public class Paper extends Object
This class is responsible to keep track of all the information that is related to the paper like the paper id, author names, type of paper, processing status, reviewer, notes, and its current state, and the class uses the state design pattern to handle the different stages of a paper, such as Submitted, Reviewing, Revising, Registering, and Closed
Author:
Steven Saleeb

  • Constructor Details

    • Paper

      public Paper(String authorNames)
      Constructs a paper with author names, the paper receives a unique id number and starts in the submitted state, it is not yet processed and sets the paper as an abstract type
      Parameters:
      authorNames - the author names for the new paper
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the author names are null or empty

    • Paper

      public Paper(int id, String state, String authorNames, String paperType, boolean processed, String reviewer, String note)
      Creates a paper with full details, This constructor is used when restoring papers that already exist and may be in any of the states it checks that the data is consistent and throws an exception if something is not right.
      Parameters:
      id - the paper id
      state - the state of the paper
      authorNames - the names of the authors
      paperType - the paper type
      processed - the processed status
      reviewer - the reviewer assign to the the paper
      note - the note of the paper
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if any information is invalid or inconsistent
